(667, 156, 39, 'Comparing the _Lord of the Rings_ trilogy and the _Hobbit_ trilogy was already like comparing apples and mediocre oranges, but none so mediocre as _Battle of the Five Armies_. Don\'t get me wrong, I love a \"battle\" as much as the next guy, more maybe, I don\'t even mind a movie that\'s 95% battle, but in this? It does. Not. Work.\r\n\r\n_Five Armies_ is a movie that never made it out of pre-viz, let alone to a polished, well-rounded, final cut. I enjoy it to some degree when running through a Middle-Earth marathon as a whole, but only when the group I\'m with will let me roll my eyes and complain about it.\r\n\r\n_Final rating:★★½ - Had a lot that appealed to me, didn’t quite work as a whole._', 3, 1, '2024-09-09 04:13:25', '2024-09-09 04:13:25', NULL),
