(1032, 170, 136, 'I believe that we should call it a modernism show, albeit exhibited in the form of a movie. While it might feel \"boring\", it forces you to rethink what philosophical level that a two-hour film can achieve. The focus on questions about life, intelligence, and time, is worth more attention than the sci-fi part (though the special effect of this movie is already way ahead of its time).', 4, 1, '2024-09-09 04:13:26', '2024-09-09 04:13:26', NULL),
